abstract: Chile's Congress on Thursday gave the green light to a referendum on changing the country's constitution next year, a central demand of protesters whose mobilizations brought the nation virtually to a standstill over the past eight weeks.
snippet: Chile's Congress on Thursday gave the green light to a referendum on changing the country's constitution next year, a central demand of protesters whose mobilizations brought the nation virtually to a standstill over the past eight weeks.
lead_paragraph: SANTIAGO — Chile's Congress on Thursday gave the green light to a referendum on changing the country's constitution next year, a central demand of protesters whose mobilizations brought the nation virtually to a standstill over the past eight weeks.
headline_main: Chilean Lawmakers Approve Popular Vote on Pinochet-Era Constitution
headline_print_headline: Chilean Lawmakers Approve Popular Vote on Pinochet-Era Constitution

abstract: An Ottawa judge on Thursday dismissed all 19 charges against former Taliban hostage Joshua Boyle, who was charged with sexual assault of his estranged wife, Caitlan Coleman.

headline_main: Canada Judge Dismisses Assault Charges Against Former Taliban Hostage
headline_print_headline: Canada Judge Dismisses Assault Charges Against Former Taliban Hostage

abstract: Boeing Co is set to launch its new astronaut capsule on Friday on its first unmanned journey to the International Space Station, a milestone test for the U.S. aerospace firm that is vying with SpaceX to revive NASA's human spaceflight capabilities.
snippet: Boeing Co is set to launch its new astronaut capsule on Friday on its first unmanned journey to the International Space Station, a milestone test for the U.S. aerospace firm that is vying with SpaceX to revive NASA's human spaceflight capabilities...
lead_paragraph: CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. — Boeing Co is set to launch its new astronaut capsule on Friday on its first unmanned journey to the International Space Station, a milestone test for the U.S. aerospace firm that is vying with SpaceX to revive NASA's human spaceflight capabilities.
headline_main: Boeing Astronaut Capsule Faces Key Test on Trip to Space Station
headline_print_headline: Boeing Astronaut Capsule Faces Key Test on Trip to Space Station

abstract: A European operation to ensure safe shipping in the Gulf region, scene of attacks on merchant vessels this year, will get underway next month when a French warship starts patrolling there, a French armed forces spokeswoman said on Thursday.
snippet: A European operation to ensure safe shipping in the Gulf region, scene of attacks on merchant vessels this year, will get underway next month when a French warship starts patrolling there, a French armed forces spokeswoman said on Thursday.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — A European operation to ensure safe shipping in the Gulf region, scene of attacks on merchant vessels this year, will get underway next month when a French warship starts patrolling there, a French armed forces spokeswoman said on Thursday.
headline_main: French Warship to Spearhead European Mission in Gulf From Next Year
headline_print_headline: French Warship to Spearhead European Mission in Gulf From Next Year

abstract: Coughlin was supposed to revive the Jacksonville Jaguars. His stringent style was not a great match with 2019.
snippet: Coughlin was supposed to revive the Jacksonville Jaguars. His stringent style was not a great match with 2019.
lead_paragraph: Tom Coughlin was hired about three years ago to revive the ragtag Jacksonville Jaguars and immediately set all the clocks in the team’s headquarters  ahead by five minutes. Even the Jaguars rookies had heard about the routine: Coughlin Time meant being at least five minutes early.

abstract: The United States began flying Mexican deportees deep into Mexico on Thursday, and senior U.S. and Guatemalan officials said Mexicans seeking U.S. refuge might be sent to the Central American nation, in a renewed effort to slash border crossings.
snippet: The United States began flying Mexican deportees deep into Mexico on Thursday, and senior U.S. and Guatemalan officials said Mexicans seeking U.S. refuge might be sent to the Central American nation, in a renewed effort to slash border crossings....
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON/MEXICO CITY — The United States began flying Mexican deportees deep into Mexico on Thursday, and senior U.S. and Guatemalan officials said Mexicans seeking U.S. refuge might be sent to the Central American nation, in a renewed effort to slash border crossings.
headline_main: U.S. Deports Mexicans Far From Border, May Send Others to Guatemala
headline_print_headline: U.S. Deports Mexicans Far From Border, May Send Others to Guatemala

abstract: The British Grand Prix at Silverstone had the biggest crowd of the 21-round 2019 Formula One season, data provided by promoters showed on Thursday, with more spectators than ever attending races.
snippet: The British Grand Prix at Silverstone had the biggest crowd of the 21-round 2019 Formula One season, data provided by promoters showed on Thursday, with more spectators than ever attending races.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The British Grand Prix at Silverstone had the biggest crowd of the 21-round 2019 Formula One season, data provided by promoters showed on Thursday, with more spectators than ever attending races.
headline_main: Silverstone on Top as F1 Reports Bigger Crowds in 2019
headline_print_headline: Silverstone on Top as F1 Reports Bigger Crowds in 2019

abstract: The Pentagon said on Thursday that it found no threat in its review of about 850 military students from Saudi Arabia studying in the United States, following a Dec. 6 shooting by a Saudi Air Force officer who killed three people at a base in Florida.
snippet: The Pentagon said on Thursday that it found no threat in its review of about 850 military students from Saudi Arabia studying in the United States, following a Dec. 6 shooting by a Saudi Air Force officer who killed three people at a base in Flori...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Pentagon said on Thursday that it found no threat in its review of about 850 military students from Saudi Arabia studying in the United States, following a Dec. 6 shooting by a Saudi Air Force officer who killed three people at a base in Florida.
headline_main: In Wake of U.S. Base Shooting Pentagon Finds No New Threat From Saudi Students
headline_print_headline: In Wake of U.S. Base Shooting Pentagon Finds No New Threat From Saudi Students
